      What's special

      Stone islandImmaculate design and formProfessional officeModern designDining and living spacePrimary bedroom suitesQuartz countertops
      Built in 2017, this striking and contemporary home entices the eye with layered San Francisco and Bay views, immaculate design and form, and exceptional living spaces. 5695 Skyline Blvd was meticulously crafted by Scott OHara, an award-winning Net Zero and High Performance custom home builder. As you enter into the grand foyer, your eyes are met with sparkling vistas. Work from home in style with a professional office on the entry level with an adjacent powder room. Float down to the great room with soaring ceilings to the main living level with an open concept kitchen, dining and living space and large view deck. Enjoy quintessential California indoor-outdoor connection on both living levels. The kitchen features bamboo cabinets, quartz countertops, stone island, SS appliances, dual sinks and large pantry. One of two primary bedroom suites completes the main living level, perfect for visiting guests, an au pair, or as a secondary living / media room. The lower level primary bedroom ensuite features a custom walk-in closet, luxurious soaking tub with a view, and private Brazilian walnut view deck. Two large bedrooms, one with another private view deck, and full bathroom complete the lower level. Enjoy the best of modern design and distinctive use of space with no spared detail.
